def: The uppermost member of the cornice of an entablature.

A small instrument containing a minute particle of a radiumcompound mounted in front of a fluorescent screen and viewed withmagnifying lenses. The tiny flashes produced by the continualbombardment of the screen by the a rays are thus rendered visible. --Spin*thar`i*scop"ic (#), a.
To deprive of carbon; to remove the carbon from.
A plastic operation for making a new lip, or for replacing alost tissue of a lip.
One who plants or who prunes trees. [Obs.] Evelyn.
Of or pertaining to Galileo; as, the Galilean telescope. SeeTelescope.
The act of impoverishing, or the state of being impoverished;reduction to poverty. Sir W. Scott.
The rotation of a limb round an imaginary axis, so as todescribe a concial surface.
